    {
      "id": "370ba289-f01d-43e2-8c11-c5ef2a84f393",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The most common way professors evaluate whether a student is at-risk or not is through direct interaction. However, this is impractical in modern HEI. While ML can be used for this, many courses have ew datapoints to actually use. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "370ba289-f01d-43e2-8c11-c5ef2a84f393",
